article.headline: IUPUI 60, UMKC 56
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. -- Robert Glenn led four IUPUI players in double figures with 15 points Saturday as the Jaguars beat Missouri-Kansas City 60-56 at Kemper Arena. It was the third-straight Summit League victory for the Jaguars, while UMKC (6-18, 2-9) fell for the fifth consecutive time. IUPUI (12-10, 5-6) led 23-22 at halftime and stretched the margin to 11 points at the 10-minute mark in the second half. The Kangaroos rallied to cut the lead to three points twice in the final minute, but fell short as the Jaguars hit 7-of-12 free throws in that span. Joining Glenn in double figures were Gary Patterson with 12 and Jon Avery and Leroy Nobles with 10 each. Bakari Lewis had a career-high 23 points for UMKC while Latreze Mushatt and Spencer Johnson both had 12.
